<br>
Bro, I am sorry, I was rude, short and down right nasty. It was very unbecoming behavior and should not be tolerated. Please forgive me.<br>
<br>
2nd:<br>
<br>
Listen folks,<br>
<br>
I know that some of you are pretty advanced in your skills. I know that some of you simply don't have the time or inclination to farm your own stuff. I also know how easy it is to go into a zone such as the commons or the bazaar and offer plats for the drops you need.<br>
<br>
But folks, if you offer crazy amounts for these items , you set a new standard. Funny things about standards, once they are set, you can't take them back. If you /ooc to the zone that you will pay 40pp for a stack of silks, then that is the new price, for everyone, forever.<br>
<br>
I know you just want to skill up and have the plats layin around so you offer the plats in exchange for the opportunity to increase your skill.<br>
<br>
But now if you wish to make the items for a friend, you are forced to charge your friends a larger amount , just to cover the cost. Also it forces others who don't have tons of plats layin around to pay insane prices or spend ours farming items. <br>
<br>
Example: my skill is only 122.<br>
<br>
1. 5 hours farming silks/pelts to make padding<br>
2. 700pp in raw materials(mq ore, water,molds)<br>
3. 100pp str buff<br>
4. 50 combines(each preceded by 3 no skill combines)<br>
5. 7 mask that resold to vender for 22pp each<br>
6. 0 skill ups<br>
<br>
<br>
See what i am saying.<br>
<br>
I farmed my padding, however if i had paid the current Xev market for padding my investment would have climbed from 800pp to 2800pp.<br>
<br>
Come on folks, 2k in lvl 3 critter drops?<br>
<br>
Have we all lost our minds.<br>
<br>
I may just stop smithing, create a druid and get em to lvl 20 or so then just farm for my livelyhood.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nope , I will keep smithing, keep farming for my goods, get my skill to 250.<br>
<br>
I will not pay more than 3pp per stack of silks, 30pp per stacks of padding, or 10pp per stack of lq/mq/hq pelts.<br>
<br>
I urge you all to do the same.<br>
<br>
We control what we pay for items. Eventually the farmers will lower the prices back to an acceptable average, but only if we stop screwin ourselves.<br>
<br>
Hollierth<br>
